&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:p-2 hx:overflow-hidden"&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download the installer:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit the official Python website at &lt;a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on the download link for the latest version of Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the installer:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once the download is complete, locate and run the installer &lt;code&gt;.exe&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sure to check the box that says &amp;ldquo;Add Python to PATH&amp;rdquo; during installation. This step is crucial for making Python accessible from the Command Prompt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow the installation prompts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify installation:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open the Command Prompt and type:
